The paper proposes an unsupervised anomaly detection framework that uses artificial intelligence techniques for fleet-based condition monitoring of machines. The paper discusses the use of generic building blocks and the incorporation of domain expertise. The paper also highlights the interpretability of the framework, which allows a domain expert to validate the predictions made by the framework. The paper uses two use-cases on an electrical machine fleet to demonstrate the applicability of the framework. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE, and cs.SE.
